@fqtyfz I am not sure exactly what your specific question is, but at first glance, this is your error:

1) Not enough direct memory. Please adjust -XX:MaxDirectMemorySize, druid.processing.buffer.sizeBytes, or druid.processing.numThreads: maxDirectMemory[268,435,456], memoryNeeded[4,294,967,296] = druid.processing.buffer.sizeBytes[1,073,741,824] \* ( druid.processing.numThreads[3] + 1 )

You need to adjust the direct memory according to the error message.

@fjy   Great! 
Thanks
Ram

@himanshug since 0.7 host, port, and service all have proper defaults to make it easier to get started.

If we change service we need to also make a note in the release notes since it could affect people expecting to use the default.

The reasoning behind having the Druid prefix was to make it easier to integrate for users that are already using curator for service discovery.
